well , of all the people i &apos;ve met , the willii was from the sierra nevada de santa marta in northern colombia , the most extraordinary .
offspring of the old tyrannian civilization populated the caribbean coastal plain of colombia , and as a result of conquest , this people moved back to an isolated volcanic massive that rises above the caribbean coastal plain .
in a bloodshed continent , these people were the only ones that were never conquered by the spain .
to this day , they &apos;re governed by a ritual priesthood , but the priesthood education is very extraordinary .
the young akolyths are separated from their families at the age of three and four , and in a shadow world of eclipse , in stone huts at the fuge of the glaciers for 18 years , and two periods of each nine years are selected , intentionally , to mimic the nine months of pregnancy they spent in their slight mother &apos;s lap , they &apos;re now spending metamorphic in the lap of the great mother .
and all the time , they &apos;re culturally introduced to the values of their society . values that say that their prayers and only their prayers , the cosmic -- or we could say the ecological -- are sustaining balance .
at the end of this amazing initiation , they &apos;re suddenly taken out one day and for the first time in their lives , at the age of 18 , they see a sunrise . and in this crystal moment of consciousness , when the sun starts to shine on the hangs of the amazing beautiful landscape , suddenly everything they learned in the abstract is amazing practice . and the priest comes back and says , &quot; see ? it &apos;s really , how i told you .
it &apos;s so wonderful . you have to protect it . &quot;
they call themselves the older brothers and say that we &apos;re responsible for the younger brothers for destroying the world .
now this level of intuition becomes very important .
whenever we think about native and landscape , we either complain rousseau and the old scaffolding of the noble wild , which is a racial thought or , on the other hand , thoreau and say , these people are more connected to nature than we are .
so , infants are not sentimental , nor are they chosen by nostalgia .
there &apos;s not a lot of space left in the malaria swells of asmat or the cold winds of tibet , but they still , through time and ritual , have shaped a mysterious nimbus of the earth that &apos;s not based on the idea of being aware of it , but on a much more subtle intuition , the idea that the earth can only exist because it &apos;s breathed into the human mind .
well , what does that mean ?
it means that a little kid from the anden growing up in the belief that the mountain is an apu spirit that determines his or her destiny will become a very different person , and have a different relationship with this resource or this place , as a little kid from montana , who grows up in the belief that a mountain is a bunch of rocks that can be rejected .
whether it &apos;s a place of a mind or a bunch of heritage , it &apos;s irrelevant .
