this question was so tangible that we decided to explore the answer and sift .
in short , a siftable is an interactive computer the size of a cookie .
they can be moved with their hand , they can perceive each other , they can capture their movements , and they have a screen and a radio receiver .
more importantly , are physical , so you can only move them like building blocks by extending hands and access .
and the sift beds are an example of a new generation of tools for manipulation of digital data .
and when these tools become more physical and develop a awareness of their movements , recognize each other and perceive the enemies of our process with them , we can start to explore new and entertaining interactions .
