and somehow , we need to create changes that reduce that to zero .
it &apos;s been constant .
just different economic changes have influenced it at all , and we need to go from rising and reducing and reducing to zero .
this equation has four factors . a little bit of multiplication . you have this thing on the left -- co2 -- that you want to get to zero , and that &apos;s going to depend on the number of people , on the services every human being uses on average , the average energy for every service and co2 that &apos;s emitted per unit of energy .
so let &apos;s look at every factor and think about how we get that to zero .
probably one of these numbers has to get very close to zero .
now this is basic algebra , but let &apos;s go through it .
first we have the population .
today , 6.8 billion people live .
